    "The adjusted bias E is computed for each modality using the following equation:E = y m • α s + y m + α m 2 • α m (10)where y m is the modality-specific performance measure, and α s, α m are the scaling factors.",
    "The optimization process addresses the challenge of overfitting while maintaining the integrity of the individual modalities.",
    "The optimization function δ s is defined by the equation:δ s = α s -α m • y m + α m 2 • α m(11)This function seeks to minimize the error across the modalities while preserving the high-dimensional structure of the data.",
    "It is instrumental in achieving an optimal balance between the core tensor and the individual modality features.",
    "For the optimization of the multimodal fusion process, the scaling function s plays a crucial role, enabling the adjustment of the contribution of individual modality performance measures y m within the fusion scheme."
  ],
